
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/vendor/rainbow/themes/github.css" />
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/app/index.built.js"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/app.css" />
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="header">
      <div class="container blurb">
        <div class="row navbar">
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            <img id="logo" src="/img/mojo-js-transparent.png"></img>
          </div>
          <div class="navlinks col-sm-6 text-right">
            <a href="/docs">Documentation</a>
            <a href="/guides">Guides</a>
            <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/mojojs">Community</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row caption">
          <div class="col-md-3"></div>
          <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
            <h2>Build beautifully crafted, and powerful web applications</h2>

            <p>
              A non-opinionated, totally customizable JavaScript framework designed for writing
              programs that scale across any platform
            </p>

              <a class="btn download-button" href="#">Download Beta</a>
              <a class="btn download-button get-started" href="#">Get Started</a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-3"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="row caption example">

          <div class="col-md-12 text-center header-muted">
            Make realtime applications with just one line of code
          </div>
          
          <div class="col-md-12">
            {{
              idePrep: {
                projectName: "Chatroom Example",
                sourceDir: __dirname + "/_examples/chatroom"
              }
            }}
          </div>


        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="social-row">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">
            {{
              browserify: {
                component: "social"
              }
            }}
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-6">
            {{
              mailingListForm:
            }}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container content core-feature">
      <div class="row text-center">
        <div class="col-md-12">
          <h3>Customizable to the bone</h3>
          <p class="subheader">
            Mojo.js was designed to be plugin-based to the core, allowing you to customize every part of it. Easily write code once that works on any platform including web, server, and mobile. Build rich applications that give your user base the best experience possible. 
          </p>
          <hr />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container content">
      

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-heart-empty"></span>&nbsp;Simple</h3>
          <p> 
            Love Backbone.js? You'll appreciate Mojo's straight-forward, coherent API. 
            <!-- explicity -->
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span>&nbsp;Compatible</h3>
          <p> 
            Mojo easily works with just about any library. Work with jQuery, Angular, React, Backbone, 
    whatever you want. Check out the available <a href="#">cross-framework plugins</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    
       <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-wrench"></span>&nbsp;Modular</h3>
          <p>
            Mojo is composed of many loosely coupled, and highly extendable libraries. Pick whatever you want to suite your application needs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flash"></span>&nbsp;Fast</h3>
          <p>
            Mojo works very well with old browsers (IE 7+), along with newer browsers. <a href="/perf">Check out the benchmarks</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-random"></span>&nbsp;Isomorphic</h3>
          <p>
            Easily write JavaScript apps that run on the server, and the browser. Check out <a href="https://github.com/mojo-js/mojojs.com">this website</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok"></span>&nbsp;Testable</h3>
          <p>
            Writing unit tests is a breeze. You can even run them in Node.js! Check out <a href="#">writing unit tests with Mojo</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="top-footer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-1"></div>
          <div class="col-md-2">
            <ul>
              <li>Documentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-2">
            <ul>
              <li>Documentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-2">
            <ul>
              <li>Documentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-5"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom-footer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-1"></div>
          <div class="col-md-5">
            <span>
              Built by <a href="http://github.com/crcn">Craig Condon</a> at
              <a href="http://classdojo.com">ClassDojo</a>
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-5">
            {{
              mailingListForm:
            }}
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-1"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </body>

  <script type="text/javascript" src="/vendor/js/rainbow-custom.min.js"></script>
</html>
